            </rs>.</p>
               <p>JAMES TOOK. I am <rs id="t18271025-33-viclabel210" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271025-33-victim203 t18271025-33-viclabel210"></join> to Mr. Clutterbuck. On the 7th of October I was following the soldiers in <placeName id="t18271025-33-crimeloc211">St. James' Park</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18271025-33-crimeloc211" type="placeName" value="St. James' Park"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18271025-33-crimeloc211" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271025-33-off208 t18271025-33-crimeloc211"></join>; Morgan spoke to me - I did not understand him, and walked on; I afterwards found I had lost my handkerchief, which was safe just before I got to the Palace. I afterwards received information, and found it at Bow-street; I had not observed the prisoner near me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18271025-33-person204">
                  PHILIP 
                  PARISH
               <interp inst="t18271025-33-person204" type="surname" value="PARISH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271025-33-person204" type="given" value="PHILIP"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271025-33-person204" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Bow-street patrol. I was in the Park on the 7th of October, noticing the persons following the soldiers. I saw the prisoner Miles press close against Took, and Wilson pressed close to him; I saw Miles take a handkerchief out of Took's pocket, and hand it to Wilson, who put it into his breeches pocket; I seized him, took it out of his pocket, and Morgan secured Miles, without his getting out of my sight.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>MILES' Defence. I was following the band - a parcel of boys were running; they said some boys were taken for picking pockets. I went to look at them, and the officer said it was me - I never saw the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>WILSON'S Defence. I went to see the band, and picked a handkerchief up off the ground.</p>
               <p>PHILIP PARISH. I had been watching them for five minutes, suspecting them - I cannot be mistaken.</p>
               <p>MILES - <rs id="t18271025-33-verdict212" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18271025-33-verdict212" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 16.</p>
               <p>WILSON - <rs id="t18271025-33-verdict213" type="verdictDescription">
